The paper presents a model for hierarchical networks for image analysis, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of biologically inspired computations and mathematical models of receptive fields suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the scale-space properties of the computational primitives, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of a prototype application for texture analysis suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the analysis of the computational primitives suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
